==English==

===Etymology===
* ''ge''- + ''potential''

===Noun===
'''geopotential'''

# ([[Meteorology]]). The [[work]] that must be done at a given [[altitude]] in raising a unit [[mass]] from [[sea level]] to that altitude against the earth's [[gravitation]]al [[field]].

